Key Match Events: Westbrook completed a four-point possession with 4:19 left in the quarter after underscoring Zubac and tipping in Jordan's second miss.
Pre-Game Insights: Michael Malone mentioned that Russell Westbrook plays harder against the Clippers.
Westbrook expressed difficulty sleeping due to the wildfires in Los Angeles.
Post-Match Reflections: Westbrook tried to channel the city's pain into rapture, growing up in South Central Los Angeles and playing for both the Clippers and Lakers.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Westbrook finished with 19 points, six rebounds and eight assists on 50% shooting.
Westbrook called his shot on a free-throw offensive rebound and celebrated with a 'rock the baby' gesture.
Others: Westbrook has matched or surpassed a scoring total of 19 points in seven other games, with better efficiency in six of them.
Westbrook has registered his 200th and 201st triple-doubles as a Nugget, including one on 100% shooting with zero turnovers.
